# ESP32 DHT11 Temperature & Humidity Monitor

A basic ESP32 project that reads temperature and humidity from a DHT11 sensor and displays the values on the Serial Monitor every 2 seconds.

## What I Learned

* `#include <DHT.h>` – Using external libraries
* `DHT dht(26, DHT11)` – Creating a DHT sensor object
* `dht.begin()` – Initializing the sensor
* `dht.readTemperature()` – Reading temperature data
* `dht.readHumidity()` – Reading humidity data
* `Serial.begin(115200)` – Starting serial communication
* `Serial.print()` and `Serial.println()` – Displaying data on the Serial Monitor
* `delay()` – Controlling the reading interval

## How It Works

The ESP32 initializes the DHT11 sensor, reads temperature and humidity every 2 seconds, and prints the values to the Serial Monitor.


